## 6. Arduino Control Hardware Pinout & Schematics

### 6.1 Microcontroller Target
* **Platform:** Arduino Mega 2560 / ESP32 with 5V logic conversion (Recommended for high I/O count and isolated hardware timer PWM).
* **Isolation:** All relay outputs and inductive loads (fans, solenoids, dampers) are isolated via optocouplers on dedicated relay boards with separate power supplies to prevent EMI/transient noise.

### 6.2 Pin Assignment Matrix

| Pin ID | Component Name | Direction | Signal Type | Function / Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **D2** | 1-Wire Temp Array Bus | Input | Digital (1-Wire) | Connects DS18B20 sensors (Lower Tank, Upper Tank, Duct Air, Ambient, Condenser Line) |
| **D3** | 10" Centrifugal Fan PWM | Output | Hardware PWM (Timer) | 25kHz PWM output to fan driver / speed controller |
| **D4** | Fan AC Power Relay | Output | Digital (Active LOW) | Opto-isolated relay enabling AC main power to centrifugal fan |
| **D5** | Motorized Damper Open | Output | Digital (Active LOW) | Drives open state for top register motorized airflow damper |
| **D6** | Motorized Damper Close | Output | Digital (Active LOW) | Drives close state for top register motorized airflow damper |
| **D7** | 3-Way Freon Solenoid Relay | Output | Digital (Active LOW) | Winter: Energized (Diverts hot gas to sub-condenser). Summer: De-energized (Bypass) |
| **D8** | AC Compressor Contactor Relay | Output | Digital (Active LOW) | Controls 2-Ton Split-System AC unit state for summer thermal charging |
| **D9** | Sensor Power Gate (VCC_SENSE) | Output | Digital (5V) | Pulsed power pin to energize moisture/leak sensors for <5ms every 10s |
| **A0** | Drain Pan Moisture Sensor | Input | Analog (0–5V) | Resistance measurement for auxiliary drain pan dual-pin sensor |
| **A1** | Bell Flare Rope Leak Sensor | Input | Analog (0–5V) | Resistance measurement for 30° bell flare rope leak detection loop |
| **A2** | Upper Nitrogen Pressure | Input | Analog (0.5–4.5V) | 0–10 PSI static pressure transducer (Nitrogen expansion space monitoring) |
| **D13** | System Alarm LED / Status | Output | Digital | Visual indicator for fault states (Leaks, Over-temp >185°F, Sensor Failure) |

